---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
const IMG = "https://d2xsxph8kpxj0f.cloudfront.net/310519663540279873/mqBaZEe8cowVKqLebSdcGQ/hawley-trex-deck-2uwLnSueruCa29BoSx4nDJ.webp";
const schemaData = [{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Trex vs. Wood Deck in Florida: Which Is Better?","datePublished":"2025-02-28","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Landon Hawley"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"Hawley Construction Co.","url":"https://hawleyconstruction.co"},"image":IMG,"url":"https://hawleyconstruction.co/blog/trex-vs-wood-deck-florida"}];
---
<Layout
  title="Trex vs. Wood Deck in Florida: Which Is Better? | Hawley Construction"
  description="Florida's climate is hard on wood decking. We compare Trex composite vs. pressure-treated wood on cost, maintenance, longevity, and ROI for Tampa Bay homeowners."
  canonical="https://hawleyconstruction.co/blog/trex-vs-wood-deck-florida"
  schema={schemaData}
  ogImage={IMG}
>
  <Navbar />
  <section class="pt-28 pb-12 md:pt-36 md:pb-16" style="background-color:var(--navy);">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <nav class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs mb-6" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.6);font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;"><a href="/" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.6);">Home</a><span>/</span><a href="/blog" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.6);">Blog</a><span>/</span><span style="color:var(--gold);">Trex vs. Wood</span></nav>
      <span class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] mb-3 block" style="color:var(--gold);font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;">Outdoor Living</span>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white mb-4 leading-tight" style="font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;">Trex vs. Wood Deck in Florida: Which Is Better?</h1>
      <p class="text-sm" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.5);font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;">By Landon Hawley &middot; February 28, 2025</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="py-16 md:py-24" style="background-color:var(--cream);">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <img src={IMG} alt="Trex deck Tampa Bay FL" class="w-full h-72 object-cover mb-10" style="border-radius:2px;" loading="eager" />
      <div style="font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.8;">
        <p>Florida's combination of intense UV exposure, high humidity, heavy rainfall, and salt air creates one of the harshest environments for outdoor wood in the country. After building dozens of decks across Tampa Bay, our recommendation is clear: <strong style="color:var(--navy2);">Trex composite decking outperforms pressure-treated wood in virtually every category for Florida homeowners.</strong></p>
        <h2 style="color:var(--navy2);font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;margin-top:2rem;margin-bottom:1rem;">Side-by-Side Comparison</h2>
        <table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
          <thead><tr style="background-color:var(--navy);color:white;"><th style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;text-align:left;font-size:0.8rem;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.05em;">Factor</th><th style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;text-align:left;font-size:0.8rem;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.05em;">Trex Composite</th><th style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;text-align:left;font-size:0.8rem;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.05em;">Pressure-Treated Wood</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid oklch(0.88 0.01 250);"><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;font-weight:600;color:var(--navy2);">Lifespan in FL</td><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;">25-30+ years</td><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;">8-12 years</td></tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid oklch(0.88 0.01 250);background-color:white;"><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;font-weight:600;color:var(--navy2);">Annual Maintenance</td><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;">Soap and water cleaning</td><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;">Stain/seal every 1-2 years</td></tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid oklch(0.88 0.01 250);"><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;font-weight:600;color:var(--navy2);">Splinters</td><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;">None</td><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;">Yes, especially as it ages</td></tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid oklch(0.88 0.01 250);background-color:white;"><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;font-weight:600;color:var(--navy2);">Installed Cost (300 sq ft)</td><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;">$13,500-$25,500</td><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;">$8,000-$15,000</td></tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid oklch(0.88 0.01 250);"><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;font-weight:600;color:var(--navy2);">Warranty</td><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;">25-year fade &amp; stain</td><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;">None (material only)</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <p>When you factor in the cost of staining and sealing wood every 1-2 years, plus the eventual replacement cost at year 10-12, Trex typically costs less over a 25-year period than pressure-treated wood — even though the upfront cost is higher.</p>
        <h2 style="color:var(--navy2);font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;margin-top:2rem;margin-bottom:1rem;">Our Recommendation</h2>
        <p>For Tampa Bay homeowners who plan to stay in their home for more than 5 years, we always recommend Trex. The zero-maintenance lifestyle, superior durability in Florida's climate, and 25-year warranty make it the clear choice. The only scenario where pressure-treated wood makes sense is if you are on a very tight budget and plan to sell the home within 3-4 years.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-12 p-8 text-center" style="background-color:var(--navy);border-radius:2px;">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-3" style="font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;">Get a Free Trex Deck Estimate</h2>
        <p class="mb-6" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.7);font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;">Serving Tampa, St. Petersburg, Clearwater, and all of Tampa Bay.</p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
          <a href="/trex-deck-builder-tampa-bay/" class="btn-gold text-center">Trex Deck Builder</a>
          <a href="/contact" class="btn-outline-light text-center">Contact Us</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
